": "https://github.com/Rust-GCC/gccrs/raw/105395ad98c7d9c0141603aa84773af5dd08a461/libjava%2FChangeLog", "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/contents/libjava%2FChangeLog?ref=105395ad98c7d9c0141603aa84773af5dd08a461", "patch": "@@ -1,3 +1,8 @@\n+2006-07-21  Mohan Embar  <gnustuff@thisiscool.com>\n+\n+\t* gnu/java/net/natPlainSocketImplPosix.cc (bind): Clear\n+\tSockAddr before using - needed for OS X/PPC.\n+\n 2006-07-21  Keith Seitz  <keiths@redhat.com>\n \n \t* boehm.cc (_Jv_SuspendThread): Don't ifdef the function declaration,"}, {"sha": "2dfc38cda5ee409585cadbdc48cc449da9f0cbfe", "filename": "libjava/gnu/java/net/natPlainSocketImplPosix.cc", "status": "modified", "additions": 5, "deletions": 0, "changes": 5, "blob_url": "https://github.com/Rust-GCC/gccrs/blob/105395ad98c7d9c0141603aa84773af5dd08a461/libjava%2Fgnu%2Fjava%2Fnet%2FnatPlainSocketImplPosix.cc", "raw_url": "https://github.com/Rust-GCC/gccrs/raw/105395ad98c7d9c0141603aa84773af5dd08a461/libjava%2Fgnu%2Fjava%2Fnet%2FnatPlainSocketImplPosix.cc", "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/contents/libjava%2Fgnu%2Fjava%2Fnet%2FnatPlainSocketImplPosix.cc?ref=105395ad98c7d9c0141603aa84773af5dd08a461", "patch": "@@ -89,6 +89,11 @@ gnu::java::net::PlainSocketImpl::bind (::java::net::InetAddress *host, jint lpor\n   int len = haddress->length;\n   int i = 1;\n \n+  // The following is needed for OS X/PPC, otherwise bind() fails with an\n+  // error. I found the issue and following fix on some mailing list, but\n+  // no explanation was given as to why this solved the problem.\n+  memset (&u, 0, sizeof (u));\n+\n   if (len == 4)\n     {\n       u.address.sin_family = AF_INET;"}]}